    PCQ/Ceil

    NAME
        Ceil - return the least whole number greater than or equal

    SYNOPSIS
        FUNCTION Ceil(Expr : Real) : Real;

    DESCRIPTION
        The Ceil function returns the least whole number, expressed
        as a Real value, greater than or equal to the number passed
        in.

    EXAMPLE

        PROGRAM ShowCeil;
        VAR
            FloatValue : Real;
        BEGIN
            Write('Please enter a Real value: ');
            Readln(FloatValue);
            Writeln(FloatValue:0:3, ' becomes ',
                            Ceil(FloatValue):0:3);
        END.

        Ceil(5.4)  =  6.0
        Ceil(-5.4) = -5.0

    INPUTS

        Expr : Any Real type expression

    RESULTS
        A Real value that is the least whole number greater than
        or equal to Expr.

    BUGS

    SEE ALSO
        @{" Floor " link "PCQ:Hyper/pcq/pcq2.guide/floor" 0} @{" Trunc " link "PCQ:Hyper/pcq/pcq4.guide/trunc" 0} @{" Round " link "PCQ:Hyper/pcq/pcq3.guide/round" 0} @{" Float " link "PCQ:Hyper/pcq/pcq2.guide/float" 0}

@endnode

